title: Augustana Men's Golf Stands Sixth At NSIC Championship
text:
Augustana Men's Golf Stands Sixth At NSIC Championship October 5, 2015, 8:38 PM 
LAKE CITY, Minn. â€“ Augustana University men's golf shot a 25-over-par 309 in the first round of the Northern Sun Intercollegiate Conference Championship and is in sixth-place out of 10 teams after 18 holes. The first two rounds of the championship are being played at the par-71, 6,669-yard The Jewel in Lake City, Minn. The NSIC men's golf championship is a 72-hole tournament that consists of two rounds in the fall and two in the spring. The spring portion of the championship will be held April 9-10 at Paradise Point Golf Complex in Smithville, Mo. Minnesota State shot a two-over-par 286 today to lead after the first round. The Mavericks hold an eight-stroke lead over St. Cloud State who shot 10-over-par 294 today. Minnesota State's Kelton Schmitz is the individual leader after a round-one score of two-under-par 69. Parker Klitzke shot four-over-par 75 in the first round today and is tied for 15th after 18 holes. Ted Urch carded a five-over-par 76 and finds himself tied for 20th. Clay Kopplin is currently tied for 28th after carding a seven-over-par 78 this afternoon. Collin Hammer and Jake Weber are both tied for 36th at nine-over-par 80 after one round. Round two of the championship will begin with a shotgun start on Tuesday at 10 a.m.
